This directly tells Terraform to replace the resource in one step.

âœ… In Interviews, say:

"terraform taint marks a resource for recreation in the next apply. Itâ€™s helpful when AWS resources become unhealthy or corrupted. For example, if an EC2 instance is stuck, I can run terraform taint aws_instance.my_ec2 and then apply to get a fresh instance."

