ğŸ‘‰ If Jenkins parameter = prod, it picks prod.tfvars and deploys to production.

ğŸ”¹ Best Practices
âœ… Always keep variables.tf to document all variables.
âœ… Use .tfvars files for environment-specific values.
âœ… Never hardcode sensitive values (use AWS SSM Parameter Store, Secrets Manager).
âœ… Use -var-file in automation pipelines.

âœ… In an interview, you can say:

